{"title_page": "On Point (song)", "text_new": "{{short description|2018 single by KSI}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = On Point\n| cover      = KSI On Point Cover.jpeg \n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]]\n| album      =\n| released   = 17 August 2018\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded   = 2018\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      =\n[[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n| length     = 4:10\n| label      =\n* [[RBC Records|RBC]]\n* [[BMG Rights Management|BMG]]{{efn|group=upper-alpha|\"On Point\" was originally released independently, but has been licensed to [[RBC Records]], under [[BMG Rights Management]], since November 2019 after KSI signed to the record label.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.musicweek.com/labels/read/artist-and-youtube-personality-ksi-signs-with-bmg/077981|title=Artist and YouTube personality KSI signs with BMG|website=[[Music Week]]|date=2019-11-05|language=en|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>}}\n| writer     =\n* [[KSI (entertainer)|Olajide Olatunji]]\n* Justin Trugman\n* Kes Ingoldsby\n* Wallis Lane\n* Nima Jahanbin\n* Paymon Jahanbin\n* Derico Stefano Mpyo<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n| producer   =\n* JT\n* Kes Knoxa\n* Wallis Lane\n* Heat On Da Beat<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n| chronology = [[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]]\n| prev_title = Slow Motion\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = Ares\n| next_year  = 2018\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|TofmKTHkAGE|\"On Point\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''On Point'''\" is a song by British YouTube personality and rapper [[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]]. The song is produced by JT, Kes Knoxa, Wallis Lane and Heat On Da Beat. It was released independently on 17 August 2018.<ref name=\"autogenerated2\" /> The song is partially a [[Diss (music)|diss track]] aimed at American YouTuber [[Logan Paul]] and was KSI's [[Entrance music|ring walk entrance music]] for [[KSI vs. Logan Paul]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/boxing/ksi-diss-track-point-takes-13113892|title=KSI diss track On Point takes rivalry with Logan Paul to new level|last=|first=|date=2018-08-21|website=[[Daily Mirror|Mirror]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/08/25/ksi-and-logan-paul-call-for-rematch-as-they-are-both-declared-the-winner-7882823/|title=KSI and Logan Paul call for rematch as they are both declared the winner|last=|first=|date=2018-08-25|website=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> \u2012 a [[White-collar boxing|white-collar]] [[amateur boxing]] match between KSI and Logan Paul on 25 August 2018 at [[Manchester Arena]], which ended in a [[majority draw]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-45310986|title=KSI v Logan Paul: YouTube boxing fight ends in a draw|last=|first=|date=2018-08-26|website=[[BBC News Online|BBC News]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n\n== Promotion ==\nOn 14 August 2018, KSI announced the upcoming release of the song by posting the song's artwork to his social media pages with the caption \"17th August\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bmd3ferB5nX/|title=17th August|last=KSI|first=|date=2018-08-14|website=[[Instagram]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> The next day, he teased the song's music video by posting a photo of himself holding a look-alike of Logan Paul's pet dog Kong, taken on the film set of the music video, with the caption \"cute dog\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BmhCJhtBWNm/|title=Cute dog \ud83d\ude08 \ud83d\udcf7: @charliewoodwardmedia|last=KSI|first=|date=2018-08-15|website=[[Instagram]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n\n== Music video ==\nThe music video, directed by Konstantin and Meji Alabi, was uploaded to KSI's [[YouTube]] channel on 17 August 2018.<ref name=\":0\" /> The video stars KSI pursuing and taunting a [[doppelg\u00e4nger]] of Logan Paul.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.dexerto.com/entertainment/ksi-releases-a-new-diss-track-music-video-with-a-logan-paul-look-alike-142234|title=KSI Releases a New Diss Track Music Video With a Logan Paul Look-alike|last=|first=|date=2018-08-17|website=Dexerto|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> The video also stars doppelg\u00e4ngers of Paul's brother [[Jake Paul]], their parents Pam Stepnick and Greg Paul, Paul's friend [[Evan Eckenrode]], Paul's manager Jeff Levin, Paul's pet dog Kong, members of YouTube group [[Team 10 (group)|Team 10]] and American boy band [[Why Don't We]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/08/18/ksi-wages-all-out-avengers-infinity-war-at-logan-paul-in-diss-track-on-point-7855533/|title=KSI drops Logan Paul diss track On Point but fans aren't happy with the video|last=|first=|date=2018-08-18|website=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" /> The video references several of Paul's controversies, such as when he [[Logan Paul#2018\u2013present: YouTube boxing; further controversies|tasered a dead rat]] in February 2018, and the [[Logan Paul#2017\u20132018: Suicide forest controversy|suicide forest controversy]] in January 2018, where Paul filmed the recently deceased corpse of a man who had died by hanging himself in [[Aokigahara]], known as the \"suicide forest\", in [[Japan]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailystar.co.uk/news/latest-news/ksi-logan-paul-diss-track-16886017|title=KSI to beat Logan Paul? British YouTuber hailed as diss track revealed ahead of fight|last=|first=|date=2018-08-18|website=[[Daily Star (United Kingdom)|Daily Star]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" /> The video also contains nods to [[Jack Torrance]] from [[The Shining (film)|''The Shining'']] and [[Thanos]] from [[Avengers (comics)|''The Avengers'']].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/8/17/17722316/ksi-logan-paul-diss-track-avengers-infinity-war-thanos-jake-paul-team-10-shining-youtube|title=KSI\u2019s Logan Paul diss track includes Avengers, Clockwork Orange and Shining references|last=|first=|date=2018-08-17|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" /> A [[Making-of|behind-the-scenes]] video of the filming of the music video was uploaded to YouTube by director Konstantin on the same day as the release of the music video.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2vWJ5D3pbvk|title=KSI - ON POINT (LOGAN PAUL DISS TRACK) Behind The Scene|last=|first=|date=2018-08-17|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> The music video accumulated around 7 million views in the first day of its release, and as of April 2020, it has 37 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BmoYaK0hRXO/|title=7 million views in a day for a music video. On point. Pure love to my bros @pimpjuicek @mejialabi \ud83d\udcf7: @charliewoodwardmedia|last=KSI|first=|date=2018-08-18|website=[[Instagram]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TofmKTHkAGE|title=KSI - ON POINT (LOGAN PAUL DISS TRACK)|last=|first=|date=2018-08-17|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n\n== Response ==\nOn 21 August 2018, three days after KSI released \"On Point\", Logan Paul uploaded a diss track against KSI titled \"Goodbye KSI\" to his YouTube channel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/08/21/logan-paul-goes-in-on-ksi-as-he-claps-back-with-his-own-diss-track-7868406/|title=Logan Paul goes in on KSI as he claps back with his own diss track|last=|first=|date=2018-08-21|website=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dexerto.com/entertainment/logan-pauls-new-diss-track-is-filled-with-awkward-old-clips-of-ksi-145684|title=Logan Paul's New Diss Track is Filled With Awkward Old Clips of KSI|last=|first=|date=2018-08-23|website=Dexerto|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> As of April 2020, it has 32 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o_ebRk1AnbE|title=KSI - GOODBYE KSI (DISS TRACK) FEAT. KSI|last=|first=|date=2018-08-21|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n\n== Track listing ==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download<ref name=autogenerated2 />\n| length5 = \n| all_writing = \n| title2 = \n| length2 = \n| title3 = \n| length3 = \n| title4 = \n| length4 = \n| title5 = \n| title6 = \n| title7 = \n| title1 = On Point\n| length7 = \n| title8 = \n| length8 = \n| title9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| length10 = \n| length6 = \n| length1 = 4:10\n| total_length = \n}}\n\n== Credits and personnel ==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/120179272/credits|title=On Point by KSI|last=|first=|date=2018-08-17|website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n{{div col}}\n*[[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]] \u2013 vocals, songwriter\n*JT \u2013 producer, songwriter\n*Kes Knoxa \u2013 producer, songwriter\n*Wallis Lane \u2013 producer, songwriter\n*Nima Jahanbin \u2013 songwriter\n*Paymon Jahanbin \u2013 songwriter\n*Derico Stefano Mpyo \u2013 songwriter\n*[[Sway (musician)|Sway]] \u2013 engineer\n*Charlie Cook \u2013 engineer\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Scotland|98|date=20180209|rowheader=true|accessdate=18 April 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|UKdownload|86|date=20180824|rowheader=true|accessdate=18 April 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|UKindie|23|date=20180824|rowheader=true|accessdate=18 April 2020}}\n|}\n\n== Release history ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\" |Region\n! scope=\"col\" |Date\n! scope=\"col\" |Format\n! scope=\"col\" |Label\n! scope=\"col\" |Ref.\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |Various\n| 17 August 2018\n| {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| [[Self-publishing|Self-released]]\n| <ref name=\"autogenerated2\">{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/gb/album/on-point-single/1483539661|title=On Point - Single by KSI|last=|first=|date=2018-08-17|website=[[Apple Music]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n*[[KSI vs. Logan Paul]]\n*[[List of diss tracks#YouTube |List of diss tracks \u00a7 YouTube]]\n\n== Notes ==\n<references group=\"upper-alpha\" responsive=\"1\"></references>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|3}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TofmKTHkAGE Music video] on [[YouTube]]\n* [https://genius.com/Ksi-on-point-lyrics Lyrics of the song] at [[Genius (website)|Genius]]\n\n{{KSI}}\n[[Category:2018 songs]]\n[[Category:2018 singles]]\n[[Category:BMG Rights Management singles]]\n[[Category:Diss tracks]]\n[[Category:KSI (entertainer) songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by KSI (entertainer)]]\n[[Category:YouTube music videos]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2018 single by KSI}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Use British English|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = On Point\n| cover      = KSI On Point Cover.jpeg \n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]]\n| album      =\n| released   = 17 August 2018\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| recorded   = 2018\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      =\n[[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n| length     = 4:10\n| label      =\n* [[RBC Records|RBC]]\n* [[BMG Rights Management|BMG]]{{efn|group=upper-alpha|\"On Point\" was originally released independently, but has been licensed to [[RBC Records]], under [[BMG Rights Management]], since November 2019 after KSI signed to the record label.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.musicweek.com/labels/read/artist-and-youtube-personality-ksi-signs-with-bmg/077981|title=Artist and YouTube personality KSI signs with BMG|website=[[Music Week]]|date=2019-11-05|language=en|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>}}\n| writer     =\n* [[KSI (entertainer)|Olajide Olatunji]]\n* Justin Trugman\n* Kes Ingoldsby\n* Wallis Lane\n* Nima Jahanbin\n* Paymon Jahanbin\n* Derico Stefano Mpyo<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n| producer   =\n* JT\n* Kes Knoxa\n* Wallis Lane\n* Heat On Da Beat<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n| chronology = [[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]]\n| prev_title = Slow Motion\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = Ares\n| next_year  = 2018\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|TofmKTHkAGE|\"On Point\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''On Point'''\" is a song by British YouTube personality and rapper [[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]]. The song is produced by JT, Kes Knoxa, Wallis Lane and Heat On Da Beat. It was released independently on 17 August 2018. The song is partially a [[Diss (music)|diss track]] aimed at American YouTuber [[Logan Paul]] and was KSI's [[Entrance music|ring walk entrance music]] for [[KSI vs. Logan Paul]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/boxing/ksi-diss-track-point-takes-13113892|title=KSI diss track On Point takes rivalry with Logan Paul to new level|last=|first=|date=2018-08-21|website=[[Daily Mirror|Mirror]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/08/25/ksi-and-logan-paul-call-for-rematch-as-they-are-both-declared-the-winner-7882823/|title=KSI and Logan Paul call for rematch as they are both declared the winner|last=|first=|date=2018-08-25|website=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> \u2012 a [[White-collar boxing|white-collar]] [[amateur boxing]] match between KSI and Logan Paul on 25 August 2018 at [[Manchester Arena]], which ended in a [[majority draw]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-45310986|title=KSI v Logan Paul: YouTube boxing fight ends in a draw|last=|first=|date=2018-08-26|website=[[BBC News Online|BBC News]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n\n== Promotion ==\nOn 14 August 2018, KSI announced the upcoming release of the song by posting the song's artwork to his social media pages with the caption \"17th August\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bmd3ferB5nX/|title=17th August|last=KSI|first=|date=2018-08-14|website=[[Instagram]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> The next day, he teased the song's music video by posting a photo of himself holding a look-alike of Logan Paul's pet dog Kong, taken on the film set of the music video, with the caption \"cute dog\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BmhCJhtBWNm/|title=Cute dog \ud83d\ude08 \ud83d\udcf7: @charliewoodwardmedia|last=KSI|first=|date=2018-08-15|website=[[Instagram]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n\n== Music video ==\nThe music video, directed by Konstantin and Meji Alabi, was uploaded to KSI's [[YouTube]] channel on 17 August 2018.<ref name=\":0\" /> The video stars KSI pursuing and taunting a [[doppelg\u00e4nger]] of Logan Paul.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.dexerto.com/entertainment/ksi-releases-a-new-diss-track-music-video-with-a-logan-paul-look-alike-142234|title=KSI Releases a New Diss Track Music Video With a Logan Paul Look-alike|last=|first=|date=2018-08-17|website=Dexerto|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> The video also stars doppelg\u00e4ngers of Paul's brother [[Jake Paul]], their parents Pam Stepnick and Greg Paul, Paul's friend [[Evan Eckenrode]], Paul's manager Jeff Levin, Paul's pet dog Kong, members of YouTube group [[Team 10 (group)|Team 10]] and American boy band [[Why Don't We]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/08/18/ksi-wages-all-out-avengers-infinity-war-at-logan-paul-in-diss-track-on-point-7855533/|title=KSI drops Logan Paul diss track On Point but fans aren't happy with the video|last=|first=|date=2018-08-18|website=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" /> The video references several of Paul's controversies, such as when he [[Logan Paul#2018\u2013present: YouTube boxing; further controversies|tasered a dead rat]] in February 2018, and the [[Logan Paul#2017\u20132018: Suicide forest controversy|suicide forest controversy]] in January 2018, where Paul filmed the recently deceased corpse of a man who had died by hanging himself in [[Aokigahara]], known as the \"suicide forest\", in [[Japan]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailystar.co.uk/news/latest-news/ksi-logan-paul-diss-track-16886017|title=KSI to beat Logan Paul? British YouTuber hailed as diss track revealed ahead of fight|last=|first=|date=2018-08-18|website=[[Daily Star (United Kingdom)|Daily Star]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" /> The video also contains nods to [[Jack Torrance]] from [[The Shining (film)|''The Shining'']] and [[Thanos]] from [[Avengers (comics)|''The Avengers'']].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/8/17/17722316/ksi-logan-paul-diss-track-avengers-infinity-war-thanos-jake-paul-team-10-shining-youtube|title=KSI\u2019s Logan Paul diss track includes Avengers, Clockwork Orange and Shining references|last=|first=|date=2018-08-17|website=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" /> A [[Making-of|behind-the-scenes]] video of the filming of the music video was uploaded to YouTube by director Konstantin on the same day as the release of the music video.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2vWJ5D3pbvk|title=KSI - ON POINT (LOGAN PAUL DISS TRACK) Behind The Scene|last=|first=|date=2018-08-17|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> The music video accumulated around 7 million views in the first day of its release, and as of April 2020, it has 37 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BmoYaK0hRXO/|title=7 million views in a day for a music video. On point. Pure love to my bros @pimpjuicek @mejialabi \ud83d\udcf7: @charliewoodwardmedia|last=KSI|first=|date=2018-08-18|website=[[Instagram]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TofmKTHkAGE|title=KSI - ON POINT (LOGAN PAUL DISS TRACK)|last=|first=|date=2018-08-17|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n\n== Response ==\nOn 21 August 2018, three days after KSI released \"On Point\", Logan Paul uploaded a diss track against KSI titled \"Goodbye KSI\" to his YouTube channel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/08/21/logan-paul-goes-in-on-ksi-as-he-claps-back-with-his-own-diss-track-7868406/|title=Logan Paul goes in on KSI as he claps back with his own diss track|last=|first=|date=2018-08-21|website=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]]|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dexerto.com/entertainment/logan-pauls-new-diss-track-is-filled-with-awkward-old-clips-of-ksi-145684|title=Logan Paul's New Diss Track is Filled With Awkward Old Clips of KSI|last=|first=|date=2018-08-23|website=Dexerto|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref> As of April 2020, it has 32 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o_ebRk1AnbE|title=KSI - GOODBYE KSI (DISS TRACK) FEAT. KSI|last=|first=|date=2018-08-21|website=[[YouTube]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n\n== Track listing ==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download<ref name=autogenerated2 />\n| length5 = \n| all_writing = \n| title2 = \n| length2 = \n| title3 = \n| length3 = \n| title4 = \n| length4 = \n| title5 = \n| title6 = \n| title7 = \n| title1 = On Point\n| length7 = \n| title8 = \n| length8 = \n| title9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| length10 = \n| length6 = \n| length1 = 4:10\n| total_length = \n}}\n\n== Credits and personnel ==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/120179272/credits|title=On Point by KSI|last=|first=|date=2018-08-17|website=[[Tidal (service)|Tidal]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n{{div col}}\n*[[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]] \u2013 vocals, songwriter\n*JT \u2013 producer, songwriter\n*Kes Knoxa \u2013 producer, songwriter\n*Wallis Lane \u2013 producer, songwriter\n*Nima Jahanbin \u2013 songwriter\n*Paymon Jahanbin \u2013 songwriter\n*Derico Stefano Mpyo \u2013 songwriter\n*[[Sway (musician)|Sway]] \u2013 engineer\n*Charlie Cook \u2013 engineer\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2018)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n