language=Chinese}}{{dead link|date=February 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n|blank1_name            = &nbsp;- Total\n|blank1_info            = [[Renminbi|CNY]] 62.174 billion (US$9.11 billion)\n|blank2_name            = &nbsp;- per capita\n|blank2_info            = [[Renminbi|CNY]] 21,439 (US$3,142)\n|blank3_name            = &nbsp;- Growth\n|blank3_info            = {{increase}} 13.9%\n|blank4_name            = [[Licence plates of the People's Republic of China|License Plate Prefixes]]\n|blank4_info            = {{lang|zh-cn|\u95fdH}}\n|blank5_name            = [[Chinese language|Local Dialect]]\n|blank5_info            = [[Northern Min]]\n|website                = {{URL|np.gov.cn}}\n|footnotes              = \n}}\n\n'''Nanping''' ({{zh|c=\u5357\u5e73|p=N\u00e1np\u00edng}}) is a third-tier<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cbnweek.com/v/article2015?id=6245 |script-title=zh:\u4e2d\u56fd\u57ce\u5e02\u5206\u7ea7|last=|first=|date=|work=| language = zh-hans|access-date=|via=CBNweekly}}</ref> [[prefecture-level city]] in northwestern [[Fujian]] [[province of China|Province]], [[China|People's Republic of China]]. It borders [[Ningde]] to the east, [[Sanming]] to the south, and the provinces of [[Zhejiang]] and [[Jiangxi]] to the north and west respectively. Part of the famous [[Wuyi Mountains]] range is located in this prefecture. Its population was 3,212,600 at the 2016 census whom 2,660,000 lived in the built-up (or metro) area made up of [[Yanping District|Yanping]] urban district.\n\nNanping is a picturesque old city, located on a hill near the fall of the Jianxi Brook into the [[Min River (Fujian)|Min]], and surrounded by high stone walls, which were used to prevent artillery fire. They formed a considerable obstacle to anything hostile in past conflicts.<ref>''Camps and Trails in China'' by Roy C. and Yvette Andrews (1918)</ref> The city flower is lily.\n\n==Administration==\nThe [[prefecture-level city]] of Nanping administers 2 [[district of China|district]]<nowiki/>s, 3 [[county-level city|county-level cities]] and 5 [[County (People's Republic of China)|counties]].\n\n*[[Yanping District]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u5ef6\u5e73\u533a}})\n*[[Jianyang District]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u5efa\u9633\u533a}})\n*[[Shaowu|Shaowu City]] ({{lang|zh|\u90b5\u6b66\u5e02}})\n*[[Wuyishan City]] ({{lang|zh|\u6b66\u5937\u5c71\u5e02}})\n*[[Jian'ou|Jian'ou City]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u5efa\u74ef\u5e02}})\n*[[Shunchang County]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u987a\u660c\u53bf}})\n*[[Pucheng County, Fujian|Pucheng County]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u6d66\u57ce\u53bf}})\n*[[Guangze County]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u5149\u6cfd\u53bf}})\n*[[Songxi County]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u677e\u6eaa\u53bf}})\n*[[Zhenghe County]] ({{lang|zh-hans|\u653f\u548c\u53bf}})\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Map\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| <div class=\"center\" style=\"position: relative\">\n{{Image label begin|image=Administrative Division Nanping.png|width=540|link=}} \n{{Image label|x=630|y=1010|scale=540/1200|text=[[Yanping District|'''Yanping''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=520|y=560|scale=540/1200|text=[[Jianyang District|'''Jianyang''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=395|y=825|scale=540/1200|text=[[Shunchang County|'''Shunchang<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=760|y=240|scale=540/1200|text=[[Pucheng County, Fujian|'''Pucheng<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=110|y=400|scale=540/1200|text=[[Guangze County|'''Guangze<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=880|y=420|scale=540/1200|text=[[Songxi County|'''Songxi<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=1000|y=580|scale=540/1200|text=[[Zhenghe County|'''Zhenghe<br>County''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=220|y=640|scale=540/1200|text=[[Shaowu|'''Shaowu<br>{{small|(city)}}''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=480|y=345|scale=540/1200|text=[[Wuyishan City|'''Wuyishan<br>{{small|(city)}}''']]}}\n{{Image label|x=740|y=760|scale=540/1200|text=[[Jian'ou|'''Jian'ou<br>{{small|(city)}}''']]}}\n</div>\n|}\n\n==Geography and climate==\n[[File:Txu-oclc-10552568-ng50-7.jpg|left|thumb|Nanping (labeled as NAN-P'ING (YENPING) {{lang|zh|\u5357\u5e73}}) (1953)]]\nNanping, similar to the rest of the province, has a [[humid subtropical climate]] ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification|K\u00f6ppen]] ''Cfa''), with short and mild winters, and long, very hot and humid summers. The monthly 24-hour average temperature ranges from {{convert|9.7|\u00b0C|1}} in January to {{convert|28.7|\u00b0C|1}} in July, and the annual mean is {{convert|19.50|\u00b0C|1}}. Rainfall averages more than {{convert|200|mm|1|abbr=on}} per month from March to June before gradually tapering off until early winter. With monthly percent possible sunshine ranging from 24% in March to 57% in July, the city receives 1,721 hours of bright sunshine annually, with summer being the sunniest time of the year; spring and late winter are especially overcast and damp.\n\n{{Weather box\n|location = Nanping (1971\u22122000)\n|metric first= Y\n|single line= Y\n|Jan record high C = 22.3\n|Feb record high C = 24.5\n|Mar record high C = 30.8\n|Apr record high C = 36.0\n|May record high C = 38.3\n|Jun record high C = 39.6\n|Jul record high C = 42.1\n|Aug record high C = 41.4\n|Sep record high C = 39.2\n|Oct record high C = 37.6\n|Nov record high C = 34.3\n|Dec record high C = 26.9\n\n|Jan high C = 14.7\n|Feb high C = 15.7\n|Mar high C = 19.4\n|Apr high C = 24.4\n|May high C = 27.9\n|Jun high C = 31.3\n|Jul high C = 34.6\n|Aug high C = 34.0\n|Sep high C = 30.9\n|Oct high C = 26.6\n|Nov high C = 21.3\n|Dec high C = 16.7\n\n|Jan low C =  6.5\n|Feb low C =  8.0\n|Mar low C = 11.4\n|Apr low C = 15.8\n|May low C = 19.5\n|Jun low C = 22.6\n|Jul low C = 24.5\n|Aug low C = 24.2\n|Sep low C = 22.0\n|Oct low C = 17.6\n|Nov low C = 12.3\n|Dec low C =  7.4\n\n|Jan record low C = \u22125.7\n|Feb record low C = \u22126.3\n|Mar record low C = \u22122.1\n|Apr record low C =  3.8\n|May record low C =  9.6\n|Jun record low C = 14.8\n|Jul record low C = 20.3\n|Aug record low C = 20.0\n|Sep record low C = 17.4\n|Oct record low C = 10.5\n|Nov record low C